Gs), constituting a 3 sigma result. 82% of the 2Jy WLRGs are\nin clusters, according to our definition (Bgq > 400) versus only 31% of the\nSLRGs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 21 Aug 2013 22:07:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-17"}
